This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3597

    ColorV is a vim plugin for dealing with colors.
    With this you can:
        Choose colors 
        Get color infos
        Edit color-texts
        Generate color lists
        Save your copied colors
        Preview color-texts in buffers
        Pick colors on screen(python2.7 and pygtk2 module needed.)
        ...
    (color-text: e.g. yellow,rgb(255,255,0),#ff3300)

    Take a glance: http://i55.tinypic.com/2jg7yu0.jpg
    Terminal(256): http://i56.tinypic.com/kb4tch.png

    Where to Start:  '<leader>cv' or :ColorV

